<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=11&amp;p=105#p105"><![CDATA[
The HTML 5.0 Doctype:<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />What is missing from the HTML 5.0 doctype:<br />1. PUBLIC keyword<br />2. DTD FPI (Formal Public Identifier)<br />3. DTD url<br /><br />I found the DTD file for the HTML 5.0 Draft. &lt;<a href="http://syntax.whatwg.org/sgml/html5core+wf2/pre1/dtd" class="postlink">http://syntax.whatwg.org/sgml/html5core+wf2/pre1/dtd</a>&gt; After reading it, This is how I think the doctype could be written:<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//WHATWG//DTD HTML 5.0 Core + Web Forms 2.0//EN&quot;<br />&quot;http://syntax.whatwg.org/sgml/html5core+wf2/pre1/dtd&quot;&gt;</code></dd></dl><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=59">wgabrie</a> — Sat Apr 07, 2007 11:54 pm</p><hr />
