Hi guys, just looking for some info on doctypes for the (x)html5 spec.<br />I'm familiar with the: <dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</code></dd></dl> <br />but I'd like to know what else you can do with this while still having the user-agent render the document in standards mode on a large range of browsers as is seen on: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://hsivonen.iki.fi/doctype/">http://hsivonen.iki.fi/doctype/</a><!-- m --><br />For example, what happens if you use one of these below.<br /><br />[1]<dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html5&gt;</code></dd></dl><br />[2]<dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html 5&gt;</code></dd></dl><br />[3]<dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE xhtml5&gt;</code></dd></dl><br />[4]<dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html foo&gt;</code></dd></dl><br />[5]<dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html foo/bar/baz&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />I read on Anne's blog  <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://annevankesteren.nl/2005/07/html5-doctype">http://annevankesteren.nl/2005/07/html5-doctype</a><!-- m --> [1] about Firefox going into quirksmode presumably from the 5 at the end. But what about [2] where there is a space, is this ok? And [5], would this work?<br /><br />I'd be interested to know what results people have obtained through any testing with similar DOCTYPES. I'd also like to know what people think about the DOCTYPE being case sensitive, I think it should be.<br /><br />Cheers Dean<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=44">Dean</a> — Mon Mar 12, 2007 10:43 am</p><hr />
